# Customer Segmentation

This project uses clustering to group customers based on their behavior and spending patterns.

The idea is simple: not all customers are the same, so treating them the same is bad business.

---

## What I did

* Explored customer data
* Cleaned and scaled features
* Used K-Means clustering to create segments
* Visualized different customer groups

---

## Dataset

Typical customer data including things like:

* Age
* Income
* Spending score

---

## Approach

K-Means clustering was used to group customers with similar patterns.
The number of clusters was chosen using the elbow method.

---

## Why this matters

Customer segmentation helps businesses:

* Target the right audience
* Improve marketing strategies
* Understand high-value vs low-value customers ([GeeksforGeeks][1])

---

## Key takeaway

Different customers behave differently.
Clustering helps make that visible.

